I am in these things.

00:11.512 --> 00:12.813
I mean, come on.

00:12.846 --> 00:15.216
Look, my calves look amazing.
I ought to wear these

00:15.249 --> 00:18.486
when I put the angel on top
of the tree, huh?

00:18.519 --> 00:20.654
So you and your family
looking forward to Christmas?

00:20.688 --> 00:22.356
I don't know.
I don't know

00:22.390 --> 00:24.358
what it's gonna be like
this year.

00:24.392 --> 00:26.394
My parents are divorced,
I'm divorced,

00:26.427 --> 00:28.729
my DVR recorded
Frosty the Snowman in Spanish.

00:28.762 --> 00:30.331
Just everything is...
everything's off.

00:30.364 --> 00:31.532
Right.
How about you?

00:31.565 --> 00:33.067
You going to Atlantic City?

00:33.101 --> 00:35.303
Man, it wouldn't be the holidays
if I didn't have

00:35.336 --> 00:38.139
Pai gow poker chips in one hand
and a comped eggnog in another.

00:38.172 --> 00:39.473
JANICE:
Hey, guys.

00:39.507 --> 00:42.276
Anyone else's elf pants
just crawling up their ass?

00:42.310 --> 00:43.311
Oh, right here!

00:43.344 --> 00:44.578
I can almost
taste mine.

00:44.612 --> 00:45.713
Mm.

00:45.746 --> 00:47.348
(laughter)

00:47.381 --> 00:49.450
Nathan, merry Christmas.

00:49.483 --> 00:53.154
Oh, wow. I didn't, uh, realize
we were doing gifts this year.

00:53.187 --> 00:56.090
You know what threw me off
was our bitter divorce.

00:56.124 --> 00:57.325
Come on. We're past all that.

00:57.358 --> 01:00.528
I just saw this, and it made me
think of our old tradition.

01:00.561 --> 01:01.529
The one
where we exchange pajamas,

01:01.562 --> 01:03.731
not the one where you,
uh, stuffed my stocking.

01:03.764 --> 01:06.267
See you outside,
Saint Nips.

01:06.300 --> 01:09.237
Ow! That's my spot!

01:09.270 --> 01:10.738
Uh-oh, I know what this is.

01:10.771 --> 01:12.506
What?

01:12.540 --> 01:14.475
Single girl flying solo
for the holidays

01:14.508 --> 01:16.110
