suede jacket.

01:51.945 --> 01:56.450
Not an easy item
to find in a boy's husky.

02:23.211 --> 02:25.213
Hey. I just put

02:25.246 --> 02:26.747
Mikayla's present
under the tree.

02:26.780 --> 02:27.781
She's gonna freak.

02:27.815 --> 02:29.950
I got her
a Surface tablet.

02:29.983 --> 02:32.920
I don't know what that is,
but she's not gonna like it

02:32.953 --> 02:35.723
any more than the Walkman
cassette player I got her.

02:38.226 --> 02:42.296
I had to go to 15 stores
before I found one.

02:42.330 --> 02:46.800
Must be really popular
this year.

02:46.834 --> 02:48.669
It's-it's a computer tablet,
Mom.

02:48.702 --> 02:50.838
Yeah, you know, like the one she
was playing with at the mall.

02:50.871 --> 02:52.740
Oh, that.
I'm not a big fan

02:52.773 --> 02:55.743
of anything that has
more answers than me.

02:55.776 --> 02:58.379
Plus, she started at it
hypnotized for 90 minutes.

02:58.412 --> 03:02.250
It was like your father
with the Lane Bryant catalog.

03:02.283 --> 03:03.384
(phone ringing)

03:03.417 --> 03:05.953
Oh, Mom,
your phone's ringing.

03:05.986 --> 03:07.488
Hey, it's Grandma.

03:07.521 --> 03:08.589
Oh, great.

03:08.622 --> 03:10.624
The woman starts talking
the second she stops dialing.

03:10.658 --> 03:12.593
When I pick up,
she'll be in the middle

03:12.626 --> 03:14.328
of a conversation
I can't get out of.

03:14.362 --> 03:18.632
...so the whole thing blew up,
and now we have no heat.

03:18.666 --> 03:22.670
I told your idiot father
not to buy that fish tank.

03:22.703 --> 03:25.406
Anyway, we should
be there tomorrow.

03:25.439 --> 03:27.541
Y-You're coming here
for Christmas?

03:27.575 --> 03:29.910
How? Dad's not even able
to get around.

03:29.943 --> 03:32.746
Bud, pick up the phone!

03:34.948 --> 03:36.650
Hello?

03:36.684 --> 03:37.818
Hi, Dad.

03:37.851 --> 03:41.389
Hey, I got
two new knees-- titanium.

03:41.422 --> 03:42.990
Look at this,
look at this.

03:43.023 --> 03:45.893
She can't see ya,
ya numbskull.

03:45.926 --> 03:47.295
She's on the phone.

03:47.328 --> 03:49.330
They're like new.

03:49.363 --> 03:50.864
Yesterday, I stepped
over a puddle.

03:50.898 --> 03:52.733
That-That's great
to hear.

03:52.766 --> 03:56.036
Did I tell you, yesterday,
I stepped over a puddle?

03:56.069 --> 03:59.340
Bud, hang up the phone!

03:59.373 --> 04:02.376
Carol, since your father
can drive again,

04:02.410 --> 04:04.778
we'll be up there
to see you for Christmas.

04:04.812 --> 04:07.315
Mom, listen,
I-I'm not so sure...

04:07.348 --> 04:09.417
No, tell me tomorrow, Carol.

04:09.450 --> 04:13.321
You're running up my phone bill
and you're boring me.

04:13.354 --> 04:15.489
Bye!

04:15.523 --> 04:17.691
Oh, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no!

04:17.725 --> 04:19.893
My parents are coming
for Christmas!

04:19.927 --> 04:21.762
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

04:21.795 --> 04:23.764
We have work to do.

04:23.797 --> 04:25.799
Put on your socks
with treads.

04:25.833 --> 04:27.935
I'll dig out
the family pictures.

04:27.968 --> 04:29.437
Hey, what the hell's going on?

04:29.470 --> 04:31.505
We have to make it look like
your father

04:31.539 --> 04:32.473
and I still live here.

04:32.506 --> 04:34.342
Mother knows
I would never put up

04:34.375 --> 04:35.609
these tacky mall
kiosk ornaments.

04:35.643 --> 04:37.345
I mean, who is Little Wayne,

04:37.378 --> 04:39.647
and why is he looking
for a ho-ho-ho?

04:42.750 --> 04:45.886
Whoa-whoa-whoa, Debbie,
what day is trash pickup?

04:45.919 --> 04:46.754
Thursday.

04:46.787 --> 04:47.788
Oh, thank goodness.

04:47.821 --> 04:49.357
I'm getting my wedding ring.

04:49.390 --> 04:51.492
For three months, I've been
trying to shoot it

04:51.525 --> 04:53.461
from across the room
into the trash can.

04:53.494 --> 04:54.328
Wouldn't you know,

04:54.362 --> 04:56.664
this is the week
I finally got the shot.

04:56.697 --> 04:59.467
W-Wait-wait a second.

04:59.500 --> 05:01.802
You haven't told Grandma yet
that you two are split up?

05:01.835 --> 05:05.339
I can't. Her neighbor Judy has
been divorced for 40 years,

05:05.373 --> 05:06.974
and my mother still
silently boos her

05:07.007 --> 05:08.108
when she takes communion.

05:08.141 --> 05:11.679
Mom, I need to point out
what a hypocrite you're being.

05:11.712 --> 05:13.581
Because when I lied to you
about my divorce,

05:13.614 --> 05:15.483
you grounded me
for three months.

05:15.516 --> 05:17.551
Which ended yesterday,
by the way.

05:17.585 --> 05:20.421
So I'd appreciate it if I could
get my Xbox back.

05:20.454 --> 05:21.689
I got the ring.

05:21.722 --> 05:24.458
And who threw away
the Lane Bryant catalog?

05:24.492 --> 05:27.561
Dad, I can't believe you're
going along with this. Why?

05:27.595 --> 05:29.830
I can't have Blanche banning me
from her lake house.

05:29.863 --> 05:31.432
It's so beautiful.

05:31.465 --> 05:34.368
You wouldn't believe
how many stars you can see.

05:34.402 --> 05:38.906
Last year, I saw
Linda Ronstadt at the bait shop.

05:38.939 --> 05:40.474
Hold on just a second.
I'm confused.

05:40.508 --> 05:41.775
If they still think
you're married,

05:41.809 --> 05:43.511
why would you still live
at this house?

05:43.544 --> 05:44.645
Yeah, they know
that you moved

05:44.678 --> 05:45.746
to Myrtle Beach
ten years ago.

05:45.779 --> 05:47.047
We all visited
at the same time.

05:47.080 --> 05:48.716
I was on
Grandma's sunscreen duty.

05:48.749 --> 05:53.387
Felt like I was massaging
damp corduroy.

05:53.421 --> 05:54.655
About a month ago,
my mother sent

05:54.688 --> 05:57.591
candied pecans down to Myrtle
Beach, and they got returned.

05:57.625 --> 05:59.560
When she called, I panicked.

05:59.593 --> 06:02.029
I told her we moved back
to Virginia to help Debbie

06:02.062 --> 06:04.097
while Adam was in rehab.

06:04.131 --> 06:05.599
Rehab?

06:05.633 --> 06:07.501
Adam doesn't even eat
sugar, let alone drink.

06:07.535 --> 06:09.169
It was for heroin.

06:09.202 --> 06:10.871
Oh, come on!

06:10.904 --> 06:13.040
It's a tangled web, honey,
and we're all in it.

06:13.073 --> 06:14.475
Nathan, you're gonna have
to call Janice

06:14.508 --> 06:15.609
and get her over here tomorrow.

06:15.643 --> 06:16.877
What?

06:16.910 --> 06:18.479
I didn't tell her
about your divorce either.

06:18.512 --> 06:19.913
Mother would kill me
if she knew

06:19.947 --> 06:21.715
I let my son give up
on his marriage.

06:21.749 --> 06:24.485
Mom, I'm not gonna
spend my Christmas lying.

06:24.518 --> 06:25.953
Hey.

06:25.986 --> 06:28.556
Uh-oh. Carol, what are
we gonna do about the kids?

06:28.589 --> 06:31.592
She's not gonna be able
to keep up with the lies. Carol?

06:31.625 --> 06:33.561
Merry Christmas, honey.

06:33.594 --> 06:36.196
Your uncle gave you
a computer tableau.

06:36.229 --> 06:38.499
Cool!

06:38.532 --> 06:40.167
CAROL: I don't even
need to say any more.

06:40.200 --> 06:41.168
She's already
in a trance.

06:41.201 --> 06:44.705
But she'll come up for air
around New Year's.

06:44.738 --> 06:45.906
Mom, I'm not doing this.

06:45.939 --> 06:47.841
You're not gonna ruin
my family's Christmas

06:47.875 --> 06:49.577
by forcing us all to tell lies.

06:49.610 --> 06:50.578
Wait, what lies?

06:50.611 --> 06:52.713
She told my grandma
you were addicted to heroin.

06:52.746 --> 06:54.615
That's not very Christmasy.

06:54.648 --> 06:57.651
Well, don't worry about it,
because we're not playing along.

06:57.685 --> 06:59.019
Yeah, me, neither.

06:59.052 --> 07:01.889
You made your bed, Mom,
now you can lie in it.

07:01.922 --> 07:04.157
Oh, really? Really?

07:04.191 --> 07:06.927
Mom's in a jam,
but she's made her bed?

07:06.960 --> 07:08.529
What about all the beds

07:08.562 --> 07:09.997
you people have made
over the years?

07:10.030 --> 07:12.165
That summer when you
gave yourself the home perm.

07:12.199 --> 07:14.502
Did I say, "Nathan,
you made your bed,"

07:14.535 --> 07:17.538
