What are they, muffins?

09:48.822 --> 09:50.724
Who wants
to see my new knees?

09:50.758 --> 09:52.993
We've moved on
from the knees, Bud.

09:53.026 --> 09:55.095
If you want
to show them off some more,

09:55.128 --> 09:57.731
go dance around in traffic.

09:57.765 --> 10:00.934
Ah, the familiar banter
of a long-lasting marriage.

10:00.968 --> 10:05.272
Marriage is a beautiful thing,
but it's damn hard.

10:05.305 --> 10:08.709
I said go dance
in traffic, Bud.

10:11.745 --> 10:15.649
It takes strength to stay
married, but you have to.

10:15.683 --> 10:17.317
God doesn't want us

10:17.350 --> 10:20.353
to be 82 years old and alone.

10:20.387 --> 10:22.823
And we don't want
to either, right?

10:22.856 --> 10:25.826
Right, Mother.
W-We don't want that.

10:25.859 --> 10:27.795
None of us want that.

10:27.828 --> 10:29.863
Oh, Janice,
Grandma wants a baby,

10:29.897 --> 10:31.832
but she doesn't want
to see us make it

10:31.865 --> 10:33.166
right in front of her.

10:33.200 --> 10:36.870
Mmm! Smells like someone's
making some muffins.

10:36.904 --> 10:38.806
I'm gonna go in the kitchen
and get me one.

10:38.839 --> 10:40.407
Here, hold this.

10:43.977 --> 10:45.078
Come on, Ray.

10:45.112 --> 10:47.414
Pick up, pick up, pick up, man.

10:47.447 --> 10:48.816
Ni hao, Nate!

10:48.849 --> 10:51.752
